The paper discusses the application of Formal Concept Analysis (FCA) to contexts with quantitative information, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of quantified contexts in recommender systems and text analysis suggests that cs.AI and cs.IR are likely sub-categories. The mention of digital image processing suggests cs.CV as another possible sub-category. The use of metrics and partially ordered sets suggests cs.DS as a likely sub-category. Finally, the focus on deriving concepts from quantitative information suggests cs.LG as a possible sub-category.
